# --- Puzzle 13: The Seven Bottles ---

on "read poem" in [logic_chamber] {
  success "You read the verse carved into the wall above the seven bottles:\n\n'Three of us are empty vessels, void of use or trick.\nOne will harm the drinker — choose that one and you'll feel sick.\nTwo will do nothing, neither help nor hinder thee.\nThe one you want stands second from the left of what is three.\nThe poison never neighbors the passage ahead.\nThe smallest of the lot holds nothing in its stead.'"
}

on "read verse" in [logic_chamber] {
